message:
What if you call an async task and want to do some UI stuff in that awaited task? For example:

```
public MyActivity : AppCompatActivity
{
...
...

protected override void OnResume()
{
	base.OnResume();
	await InitModel();
}

private async Task InitModel()
{
	mModel = await mClient.GetModel(...);
	if (mModel == null)
	{
		// Any UI operation
		mErrorText.Text = "Error loading data.";
	}
}

...
...
...

}
```

It seems this still works even though InitModel() is running on a worker thread. I read your answer to Ashutosh that is related, but I'm not sure whether this is good practise or whether I should be enclosing these UI operations in Activity.RunOnUIThread().
